<http://www.GideonOnline.com>

Burkina Faso: Background Information on Yellow Fever
----------------------------------------------------
[The following information has been extracted from the Gideon Database]
Burkina Faso is designated an "Infected Area". Yellow fever is currently or
recently reported in Gaoua Region (Batie District).
2 cases were reported in 1926; 10 in 1931; 1 in 1932.
87 cases were reported (and 3000 estimated) in 1969; but none during the
period 1970 to 1982.
356 (286 fatal) were reported in 1983; the true number was estimated at 12
500, with 3000 deaths.
17 cases (16 fatal) were reported in 1984 (southeast region); 7 in 1985
(southeast region).
No cases were reported during the period 1987 to 1997.
2 cases (1 fatal) were reported in Batie District (Gaoua Region) in 1998;
none during the period 1999 to 2002.
Immunization
----------
Routine immunization is given to the local population at age 9 months.
Vaccine coverage was:
65 percent in 1990;
78 percent in 1991;
41 percent in 1992;
42 percent in 1993;
45 percent in 1994;
55 percent in 1995;
27 percent in 1997;
47 percent in 1998;
33 percent in 1999;
56 percent in 2000;
52 percent in 2001.
Proof of vaccination is required for all travelers over 1 year of age. The
United States Centers for Disease Control (CDC) recommends vaccination for
all travelers over 9 months of age (arriving from any country).
